news.title: New home prices in China rise by 0.27% in March 2024
news.para: The average new home price across 100 cities rose 0.27% on month in March, the biggest rise since July 2021, showed data from real estate researcher China Index Academy. That compared with a 0.14% on-month gain in February.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board directors fail to meet for 10 months
news.para: Hitesh Puri, chairman, Crawfed, said, “The committee was set up last year after directions from the UT administrator to officials to re-examine the issue of need-based changes. It also made recommendations to the effect and the board has to take a call on these.

news.title: Ghost town: No takers for nearly 7,000 flats in Chennai's Ennore
news.para: 6,877 EWS flats in Ennore remain unoccupied due to poor air quality. TNHB handed the complex to TNUHDB for allotment to evicted residents. Concerns raised by TNPCB, activists, and residents have led to future stricter rules.

news.title: Pune civic body to demolish 46 dilapidated wadas before monsoon
news.para: PMC plans to demolish 46 dilapidated wadas in prime city locations like Ganesh Peth, Ghorpade Peth, and Mangalwar Peth. Seeking police intervention due to tenant opposition and fear of losing rights.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad: Four landowners booked for dumping construction waste along Pavana river
news.para: The four landowners dumped the material on the bank of the river in the Rahatni area between March 23 and 27. The civic officials, after verifying the complaints received from citizens in this regard, lodged a complaint with the police.

news.title: Bhopal civic body collects property tax worth Rs 470 crore in FY24
news.para: BMC property tax collection was about Rs 240 crore, while water cess for the financial year was about Rs 70 crore, according to sources.

news.title: Property registration revenue up over 12% in Madhya Pradesh in FY24
news.para: Revenue collection from property registrations across 15 districts in Indore-Ujjain divisions were higher by around Rs 489 crore to Rs 4,304 crore in the financial year 2023-24 that ended on March 31.

news.title: Collection of property taxes keep Ludhiana civic body officials busy on March 31
news.para: The officials claimed that online recovery was ongoing till midnight and the final tally would be done on Monday when the field staff would also share their recovery data. The officials are expecting to generate at least Rs 137 crore from property tax.

news.title: Bidhannagar civic body extends property tax deadline till April 7
news.para: They also plan to start collecting property tax in wards 27, 28, 35 and 36, covering Mahisbathan, Polenite, Nayapatti and vast bheri areas off EM Bypass, where residents are still paying ‘khajna’ or land revenue to the local panchayat or BLRO.

news.title: Ready reckoner rates to remain unchanged in Maharashtra in FY25
news.para: Satyanarayan Bajaj, deputy secretary, Maharashtra revenue department, issued a notification on March 31 conveying the state government's decision to maintain the status quo on ready reckoner rates.

news.title: Registration of properties in Mumbai rises 8% in March 2024: Report
news.para: Knight Frank India Chairman and Managing Director Shishir Baijal said, "The residential real estate sector in Mumbai has continued to perform exceptionally well in March.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP wants dues recovered from four builders
news.para: In a meeting held on Feb 16, which was chaired by deputy commissioner Nishant Kumar Yadav, it was strictly instructed that if any builder does not cooperate with the structural audit, the DRO will recover the audit amount in form of land revenue arrears.

news.title: Over 1,300 homes get registered in Greater Noida in March 2024
news.para: Altogether, the implementation of recommendations of Amitabh Kant committee on legacy stalled projects has paved the way for the registration of 15,000 flats in 94 projects in Greater Noida, it said in a statement.

news.title: HCC divests entire equity shareholding in HREL
news.para: "Hindustan Construction Company Ltd has divested its entire equity shareholding in HREL Real Estate Ltd, a wholly owned subsidiary of the company vide share purchase agreement executed on March 31, 2024," it said.

news.title: Vikram Aggarwal in talks to buy Chennai's Clarion Hotel for Rs 180 crore
news.para: The Clarion Hotel President, situated on Radhakrishnan Salai Road near the city centre and Marina Beach, has 129 rooms.

news.title: Consumer forum orders builders to compensate Parsvnath Exotica buyers for failing to give possession
news.para: The coram of the commission noted that the opposite parties (Parsvnath Buildwell, Parsvnath Developers and Devidayal Aluminium Industries) did not have a valid licence to construct the flat but kept misguiding the complainants.

news.title: Registries push up stamp revenue in Gautam Buddh Nagar by Rs 500 crore
news.para: According to data from the department, revenue rose by 18.8% from Rs 3,018 crore in the previous fiscal to Rs 3,585 crore in 2023-24.

news.title: Noida: Pay 25% dues for registry, builder told after residents of Gardenia Glory protest
news.para: On Tuesday, TOI reported the protest by residents where they had put up 'no registry no votes' posters in the society. Kailash Pandey, a resident of Gardenia Glory, said there were 1,450 flats across 20 towers in the society.
